A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 26, 2025, as Self-Direction Day; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, self-direction is an optional model of home and community-based service
3 (HCBS) delivery that enables individuals of all ages, with all types of disabilities, to maintain
4 their independence at home in their local community; and
5 WHEREAS, when an individual chooses to self-direct, they decide how, when, and from
6 whom their services and paid supports will be delivered; self-direction gives individuals the
7 freedom of choice and self-determination about their services and supports to live
8 independently in their own homes and communities; and
9 WHEREAS, the central goal of self-direction is to maximize an individual's opportunities
10 to live independently in the most integrated community-based setting of his or her choice;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, self-direction strategies shift control over resources and staffing to the
13 individual, allowing each person to determine the role that service providers will play in his
14 or her life; and
